AWARD-WINNING actress Linda Sokhulu has joined popular SABC 2 soapie, 7de Laan. The talented actress, best known for her role as Cleo on Generations, has joined the show as Tumi Selepe. According to producers, Tumi is an eloquent, confident and assertive woman from a wealthy family. “She is the youngest of four siblings, who lost her mother at the age of seven. Her father, a polygamist, runs numerous successful businesses in which her siblings are involved, but Tumi chose a different path and opted to further her studies,” read the statement. “She is a medical doctor and being the ambitious woman she is, she went back to university and studied to become a lawyer.” ALSO READ | KHANYISA TITUS OPW JOURNEY ENDS Producers further revealed that Tumi, whose relationship track record is not the most romantic, would enter into the show on a mission to search for answers surrounding her mother’s death when something her father’s first wife said triggered her to look deeper into the matter. “Tumi desperately hopes that her grandmother, an unseen but familiar favourite in Hillside, will shed light on the situation. She settles in Hillside and builds strong relationships, but remains determined to solve the mystery of her past.” Linda has played in popular productions such as uMkhokha andRhythm City.